Two Texas teenagers were killed Friday night after their car crossed over the median and into oncoming traffic.

Taylar Lesser, 17, and Nathaniel Gomez, 18, of Cedar Park, were traveling north on Parmer lane when they hit a Volkswagen in the oncoming lane. It is not clear why they drove over the median.

The teenagers died at the scene.

