Crowds of friends and family visited the crash site in Cedar Park on Saturday to mourn the tragic loss of the high school sweethearts.

They set up a memorial with balloons, crosses and pictures.

‘We found out this morning at 4am when we got a knock on the door,’ Gomez' mother Michelle Gonzales, told KVUE.

‘I knew it couldn't have been my Nathaniel, but it was,’ the grieving mother said.

